&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;● Translate customer assembly processes into BuildOS workflows&lt;br&gt;● Create and structure work instructions from CAD and engineering data&lt;br&gt;● Lead onboarding and drive adoption during pilots and early deployments&lt;br&gt;● Act as a trusted advisor to manufacturing, engineering, and operations teams&lt;br&gt;● Identify inefficiencies in customer workflows and propose improvements&lt;br&gt;● Partner with product and engineering to surface high-impact feedback&lt;br&gt;● Support demos, technical evaluations, and customer check-ins&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;● Background in mechanical, manufacturing, or industrial engineering&lt;br&gt;● Experience working in or closely with manufacturing environments&lt;br&gt;● Strong intuition for how things are built in the real world&lt;br&gt;● Ability to break down and structure complex assembly workflows&lt;br&gt;● Excellent communication skills across technical and non-technical audiences&lt;br&gt;● High ownership and comfort working directly with customers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Background&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;● Experience with CAD tools (NX, SolidWorks, Creo, etc.)&lt;br&gt;● Familiarity with PLM / ERP systems and manufacturing workflows&lt;br&gt;● Understanding of EBOM / MBOM concepts and production processes&lt;br&gt;● Experience creating or managing work instructions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
